      30                 :            : /*
      31                 :            :  * Computes elevation of a grid map from a raw point cloud.
      32                 :            :  * The algorithm divides the point cloud into cells (in x and y direction)
      33                 :            :  * that are the same size as the grid map cells. Then it looks for clusters
      34                 :            :  * of points in each of those cells and computes their mean. Mean of a cluster
      35                 :            :  * with minimal z value out of all clusters inside a cell is taken to
      36                 :            :  * be the elevation in the grid map. This allows the algorithm to also work
      37                 :            :  * indoors. All the calculations are performed in the point cloud frame.
      38                 :            :  */
